<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	You acknowledge that (i)&nbsp;upon a violation of any of the covenants contained in Section 8 of this Agreement or (ii)&nbsp;if the Company is terminating your employment for Cause, the Company would as a result sustain irreparable harm, and, therefore, you agree that in addition to any other remedies which the Company may have, the Company shall be entitled to seek equitable relief including specific performance and injunctions restraining you from committing or continuing any such violation; and
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	9.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 29.4PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Offset.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Any Severance or other payments or benefits made to you under this Agreement may be reduced, in the Company&#x2019;s discretion, by any amounts you owe to the Company provided that any such offsets do not violate Code Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;To the extent you receive severance or similar payments and/or benefits under any other Company plan, program, agreement, policy, practice, or the like, or under the WARN Act or similar state law, the payments and benefits due to you under this Agreement will be correspondingly reduced on a dollar-for-dollar basis (or vice-versa) in a manner that complies with Code Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	10.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 26.1PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Notice.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;Any notice that the Company is required to or may desire to give you shall be given by personal delivery, recognized overnight courier service, email, telecopy or registered or certified mail, return receipt requested, addressed to you at your address of record with the Company, or at such other place as you may from time to time designate in writing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any notice that you are required or may desire to give to the Company hereunder shall be given by personal delivery, recognized overnight courier service, email, telecopy or by registered or certified mail, return receipt requested, addressed to the Company&#x2019;s Chief Executive Officer at its principal office, or at such other office as the Company may from time to time designate in writing.&nbsp;&nbsp;The date of actual delivery of any notice under this Section 10 shall be deemed to be the date of delivery thereof.
</FONT>

	&nbsp;No provision of this Agreement may be amended or waived unless such amendment or waiver is agreed to by you and the Company in writing.&nbsp;&nbsp;No waiver by you or the Company of the breach of any condition or provision of this Agreement will be deemed a waiver of a similar or dissimilar provision or condition at the same or any prior or subsequent time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except as expressly provided herein to the contrary, failure or delay on the part of either party hereto to enforce any right, power, or privilege hereunder will not be deemed to constitute a waiver thereof.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event any portion of this Agreement is determined to be invalid or unenforceable for any reason, the remaining portions shall be unaffected thereby and will remain in full force and effect to the fullest extent permitted by law.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	EXHIBIT A
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	SEPARATION AGREEMENT AND GENERAL RELEASE OF ALL CLAIMS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	This Separation Agreement and General Release, dated [DATE] (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#x201D;),&nbsp;&nbsp;is made pursuant to that certain Severance Agreement dated [DATE] (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Severance Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#x201D;) entered into by and between [NAME] ("
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	") on the one hand, and TRACON Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	"), on the other.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Agreement is entered into in consideration for and as condition precedent to the Company providing separation benefits to Employee pursuant to the Severance Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is understood and agreed that the Company is not otherwise obligated to provide such benefits under the terms of the Severance Agreement and that the Company is doing so as a direct result of Employee&#x2019;s willingness to agree to the terms hereof.&nbsp;&nbsp;Collectively, Employee and the Company shall be referred to as the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Parties
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	."
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee was formerly employed by the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee's employment with the Company ended effective [DATE] (the "Termination Date").&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The purpose of this Agreement is to resolve any and all disputes relating to Employee's employment with the Company, and the termination thereof (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Disputes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	").&nbsp;&nbsp;The Parties desire to resolve the above-referenced Disputes, and all issues raised by the Disputes, without the further expenditure of time or the expense of contested litigation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the Parties desire to resolve any known or unknown claims as more fully set forth below.&nbsp;&nbsp;For these reasons, they have entered into this Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employee acknowledges and agrees that Employee has received all wages due to Employee through the Termination Date, including but not limited to all accrued but unused vacation, bonuses, commissions, options, benefits, and monies owed by the Company to Employee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee further agrees and acknowledges that Employee has been fully paid and reimbursed for any and all business expenses which Employee incurred during his/her employment with the Company.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company expressly denies any violation of any federal, state or local statute, ordinance, rule, regulation, policy, order or other law.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company also expressly denies any liability to Employee.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Agreement is the compromise of disputed claims and nothing contained herein is to be construed as an admission of liability on the part of the Company hereby released, by whom liability is expressly denied.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, while this Agreement resolves all issues referenced herein, it does not constitute an adjudication or finding on the merits of the allegations in the Disputes and it is not, and shall not be construed as, an admission by the Company of any violation of federal, state or local statute, ordinance, rule, regulation, policy, order or other law, or of any liability alleged in the Disputes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	5.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	In consideration of and in return for the promises and covenants undertaken by the Company and Employee herein and the releases given by Employee herein:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:93.6PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	a.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	[The Company has previously granted to Employee the following options (collectively, the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;) to purchase shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Shares
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;) under the Company&#x2019;s 2011 Equity Incentive Plan (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;):&nbsp; [List all Option Grants].&nbsp; As of the Termination Date of [DATE], a total of [_______] shares underlying Employee's stock options are vested (collectively, the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Vested Stock Options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	").&nbsp; The&nbsp;remaining shares underlying Employee's stock options are unvested and have been forfeited and canceled as of the Termination Date.&nbsp; Employee has until the date that is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	ninety (90) days after the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination Date to exercise any or all of the Vested Options (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Option Termination Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#x201D;).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; Any portion of Employee's Vested Stock Options that remain unexercised as of the Option Termination Date shall be forfeited and canceled as of such date.]
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 1PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Exhibit A-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<A NAME="eolPage168"></A>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 7PT;TEXT-INDENT:93.6PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	b.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	In addition to any compensation otherwise due Employee for actual work performed up to and including the Termination Date, Employee shall receive severance compensation as outlined in Section 2(a) of the Severance Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Pursuant to Section 2(a) of the Severance Agreement, Employee will receive a total sum of $_______, less standard withholdings, representing [_____] month[s] of Employee&#x2019;s base salary (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Severance Pay
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Severance Pay shall be paid to Employee in cash, in substantially equal monthly installments, payable over the [_____] month period following the Termination Date; provided, however, the first payment shall be made on the 60
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:6PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	day following the Termination Date and such first installment shall be in an amount to cover the first two months following the Termination Date (for avoidance of doubt such amount may only be one month of compensation if the amount being provided to Employee is arising under Section 2(a)(i) of the Severance Agreement).&nbsp;&nbsp;As a condition to receiving and continuing to receive the Severance Pay, Employee must (i) within but not later than forty-five (45) days after the Termination Date, execute (and not revoke) and deliver to the Company this Agreement and (ii) remain in full compliance with this Agreement and the Severance Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall not be entitled to accrue any additional leave or other benefits subsequent to the Termination Date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 7PT;TEXT-INDENT:93.6PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	c.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Provided Employee timely elects continuation coverage pursuant to the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act of 1985 ("
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	COBRA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	") of the Company's group health plan, the Company shall pay the entire applicable premiums to continue Employee's existing medical and dental benefits through [DATE], which represents [_____] month[s] following the Termination Date.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thereafter, Employee shall be eligible to continue his or her medical and dental benefits at his or her own cost in accordance with COBRA.&nbsp;&nbsp;If at any time subsequent to the Termination Date, Employee obtains medical and dental benefits through another employer, Employee shall immediately notify the Company that he or she has obtained such medical and dental benefits and the Company shall no longer be required to pay any premiums for Employee's medical and dental benefits as of the date that Employee's new medical and dental benefits begin coverage.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 7PT;TEXT-INDENT:93.6PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	d.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Any tax liabilities resulting from or arising out of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	benefits
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	to Employee referred to in paragraphs 5a, 5b and 5c, above, shall be the sole and exclusive responsibility of Employee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee agrees to indemnify and hold the Company and the others released herein harmless from and for any tax liability (including, but not limited to, assessments, interest, and penalties) imposed on the Company by any taxing authority on account of the Company failing to withhold for tax purposes any amount from the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	benefits
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	made as consideration of this Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 7PT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	6.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Except for any rights created by this Agreement, i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	,

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	&nbsp;(

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	) parking
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	passes

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Expansion Premises)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, all of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	passes
</FONT>

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN BOLD;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	EXHIBIT B
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	TENANT WORK LETTER
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This Tenant Work Letter shall set forth the terms and conditions relating to the construction of the tenant improvements in the Expansion Premises which shall be referred to herein as the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Premises
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	".&nbsp;&nbsp;This Tenant Work Letter is essentially organized chronologically and addresses the issues of the construction of the Premises, in sequence, as such issues will arise during the actual construction of the Premises.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1015AF448_HTM_OLE_LINK1">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All references in this Tenant Work Letter to Sections of "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	this Amendment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	" shall mean the relevant portion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fourth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Amendment to which this Tenant Work Letter is attached as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Exhibit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	B
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and of which this Tenant Work Letter forms a part, all references in this Tenant Work Letter to Articles or Sections of "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	this Lease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	" shall mean the relevant portions of the Lease (as amended) being amended by this Amendment, and all references in this Tenant Work Letter to Sections of "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	this Tenant Work Letter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	" shall mean the relevant portions of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Sections 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of this Tenant Work Letter.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;All references in this Tenant Work Letter to the "Premises" shall mean the "Expansion Premises."
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	SECTION 1
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	DELIVERY OF PREMISES; TENANT IMPROVEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Delivery of Premises
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Landlord shall delivery possession of the Premises to Tenant on or before December 1, 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tenant hereby acknowledges that the Premises are currently occupied by another tenant of the Building.&nbsp;&nbsp;If Landlord is unable for any reason to deliver possession of the Premises to Tenant on any specific date, then Landlord shall not be subject to any liability for its failure to do so, and such failure shall not affect the validity of this Lease or the obligations of Tenant hereunder; provided, however, the date set forth in Section 2(ii) of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	this Fourth Amendment shall be delayed until the date that is thirty (30) days after the date Landlord delivers possession of the Premises to Tenant.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	If Landlord does not deliver possession of the Premises to Tenant by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	March
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1, 2016 (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Outside Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	"), then the sole remedy of Tenant for such failure shall be the right to deliver a notice to Landlord (a "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Termination Notice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	") electing to terminate th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Lease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with respect to the Expansion Premises only
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	effective upon the date occurring five (5) business days following receipt by Landlord of the Termination Notice (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Effective Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	").&nbsp;&nbsp;The Termination Notice must be delivered by Tenant to Landlord, if at all, not earlier than the Outside Date nor later than five (5) business days after the Outside Date.&nbsp;&nbsp;The effectiveness of any such Termination Notice delivered by Tenant to Landlord shall be governed by the terms of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&nbsp;1.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;If Tenant delivers a Termination Notice to Landlord, then Landlord shall have the right to suspend the occurrence of the Effective Date for a period ending thirty (30) days after the Effective Date by delivering written notice to Tenant, prior to the Effective Date, that, in Landlord's reasonable, good faith judgment,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord will deliver the Premises to Tenant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	within thirty (30) days after the Effective Date (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Termination Extension Notice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	").&nbsp;&nbsp;If
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord delivers the Premises to Tenant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	within such thirty (30) day suspension period, then the Termination Notice shall be of no force or effect, but if
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord does not deliver the Premises to Tenant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	within such thirty (30) day suspension period, then the Lease with respect to the Expansion Premises shall terminate upon the expiration of such thirty (30) day suspension period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Upon any termination as set forth in this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&nbsp;1.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, Landlord and Tenant shall be relieved
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 1PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	from any and all liability to each other resulting hereunder
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with respect to the Expansion Premises,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	except that Landlord shall return to Tenant any prepaid rent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with respect to the Expansion Premises and Landlord shall return the additional Security Deposit amount
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	paid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	by Tenant pursuant to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&nbsp;8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the Fourth Amendment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Tenant Improvements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	If Tenant desires to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	construct
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	improvements in the Premises (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Tenant Improvements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	")
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, then Tenant shall have the right to deliver
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	space plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(a "Space Plan") to Landlord depicted such Tenant Improvements, which Space Plan shall be subject to Landlord's approval, which shall not be unreasonably withheld
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Following
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord's approval of the Space Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, Tenant shall cooperate in good faith with Landlord&#x2019;s architects and engineers to supply such information necessary to allow Landlord&#x2019;s architects and engineers to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	prepare
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	architectural and engineering drawings for the Premises in a form which is complete to allow subcontractors to bid on the work and to obtain all applicable permits
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and in a manner consistent with, and which are a logical extension of, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pace
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	P
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	lan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(collectively, the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Original
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Working Drawings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and Landlord shall submit the Original Working Drawings to Tenant for its approval, which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shall not be unreasonably withheld
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Following Tenant's
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approval of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Original
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Working Drawings, Landlord shall
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	provide Tenant with a cost proposal (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Cost Pricing Proposal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	") in accordance with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Original
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Working Drawings for the Premises, which cost proposal shall include, as nearly as possible, the cost to be incurred in connection with the perform
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ance of the Tenant Improvements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Within five (5) business days, Tenant shall either (i) approve the Cost Pricing Proposal or (ii) disapprove the Cost Pricing Proposal and provide Landlord with Tenant's proposed revisions to the same
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which proposed revisions shall be subject to Landlord's approval, not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon Landlord's receipt of Tenant's approval of the Cost Pricing Proposal or upon Tenant's failure to timely delivery notice of its approval of the same,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord shall construct the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Tenant Improvements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pursuant to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Original
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Working Drawings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the event that Tenant disapproves of the Cost Pricing Proposal, Landlord shall cause its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	architects and engineers to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	modify the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Original Working Drawings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in a manner consistent with, and which are a logical extension of Tenant's proposed revisions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thereafter, Landlord shall construct the Tenant Improvements pursuant to such modified
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Original
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Working Drawings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Modified Working Drawings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	")
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As used in this Tenant Work Letter, the term "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Approved Working Drawings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	" shall mean either the Original Working Drawings or the Modified Working Drawings, as applicable.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Except as set forth above,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Tenant shall make no changes or modifications to the Approved Working Drawings, without the prior written consent of Landlord.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord shall
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	cause the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Premises
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to comply with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pplicable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	l
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	aws, at Landlord's sole cost and expense, to the extent required in order to allow Tenant to obtain a certificate of occupancy
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or its legal equivalent, for the Premises for general office use assuming a normal and customary office occupancy density
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	No Constructive Eviction
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	If all or any portion of the Tenant Improvements shall be constructed by Landlord on or after the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Expansion Commencement Date
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, then (i) Landlord shall be permitted to complete the Tenant Improvements during normal business hours, (ii) Tenant shall provide a clear working area for the construction of the Tenant Improvements, and (iii) Tenant shall cooperate with all reasonable Landlord requests made in connection with Landlord's completion of the Tenant Improvements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tenant hereby acknowledges that the construction the Tenant Improvements during Tenant's occupancy of the Premises shall in no way constitute a
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 1PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
	&nbsp;

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	constructive eviction of Tenant nor entitle Tenant to any abatement of rent or damages of any kind (including damages relating to any interference with Tenant's business at the Premises).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 1PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	SECTION 2
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	OVER-ALLOWANCE AMOUNT
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord has allocated an amount (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Tenant Improvement Allowance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;) not to exceed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Nine
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Thousand
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Hundred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Eighty-Five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	/100 Dollars ($
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	9,585.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	i.e.,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for each of the rentable square feet of the Expansion Premises)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the costs of designing and constructing the Tenant Improvements.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event that Landlord reasonably anticipates that the total cost of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	designing and constructing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the Tenant Improvements will exceed the Tenant Improvement Allowance, the amount of such reasonably anticipated excess shall be paid by Tenant to Landlord immediately upon Landlord&#x2019;s request as an over-allowance amount (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Over-Allowance Amount
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	").&nbsp;&nbsp;The Over-Allowance Amount shall be disbursed by Landlord prior to the disbursement of any remaining portion of Landlord's contribution to the construction of the Tenant Improvements.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event that after Tenant's
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approval of the Approved Working Drawings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, any revisions, changes, or substitutions shall be made to (i) the Approved Working Drawings (once the same are completed), or (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) the Tenant Improvements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, then any additional costs which arise in connection with such revisions, changes or substitutions shall be paid by Tenant to Landlord immediately upon Landlord's request as an addition to the Over-Allowance Amount.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the event that the Tenant Improvement Allowance is not fully disbursed by Landlord to, or on behalf of, Tenant on or before July 1, 2016, then such unused amounts shall revert to Landlord, and Tenant shall have no further rights with respect thereto; provided, however, Tenant may, pursuant to written notice delivered to Landlord on or before December 31, 2015, elect to apply all or a portion of the Tenant Improvement Allowance as an offset against Base Rent next due and owing by Tenant under the terms of the Lease, as amended hereby.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	SECTION 3
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	CONTRACTOR'S WARRANTIES AND GUARANTIES
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord hereby assigns to Tenant all warranties and guaranties by the contractor who constructs the Tenant Improvements (the "
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Contractor
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	") relating to the Tenant Improvements, and Tenant hereby waives all claims against Landlord relating to, or arising out of the construction of, the Tenant Improvements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	provided, however, that if, within 30 days after
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ubstantial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ompletion of the Tenant Improvement Work, Tenant provides notice to Landlord of any non-latent defect in the Tenant Improvements, or if, within
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	eleven (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	months after
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ubstantial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ompletion of the Tenant Improvement Work, Tenant provides notice to Landlord of any latent defect in the Tenant Improvements, then Landlord shall promptly cause such defect to be corrected
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:7PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	SECTION 5
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	MISCELLANEOUS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Tenant's Entry Into the Premises Prior to Substantial Completion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Provided that Tenant and its agents do not interfere with Contractor's work in the Building and the Premises, Contractor shall allow Tenant access to the Premises prior to the Substantial Completion of the Premises for the purpose of Tenant installing overstandard equipment or fixtures (including Tenant's data and telephone equipment) in the Premises.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to Tenant's entry into the Premises as permitted by the terms of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section 5.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, Tenant shall submit a schedule to Landlord and Contractor, for their approval, which schedule shall detail the timing and purpose of Tenant's entry.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tenant shall hold Landlord harmless from and indemnify, protect and defend Landlord against any loss or damage to the Building or Premises and against injury to any persons caused by Tenant's actions pursuant to this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section 5.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Tenant's Representative
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tenant has designated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Arlene Bolz
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as its sole representative with respect to the matters set forth in this Tenant Work Letter, who, until further notice to Landlord, shall have full authority and responsibility to act on behalf of the Tenant as required in this Tenant Work Letter.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Landlord has designated Michael Coleman as its sole representative with respect to the matters set forth in this Tenant Work Letter, who, until further notice to Tenant, shall have full authority and responsibility to act on behalf of the Landlord as required in this Tenant Work Letter.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Time of the Essence in This Tenant Work Letter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless otherwise indicated, all references herein to a "number of days" shall mean and refer to calendar days.&nbsp;&nbsp;In all instances where Tenant is required to approve or deliver an item, if no written notice of approval is given or the item is not delivered within the stated time period, at Landlord's sole option, at the end of such period the item shall automatically be deemed approved or delivered by Tenant and the next succeeding time period shall commence.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Tenant's Lease Default
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary contained in this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fourth Amendment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, if an event of default as described in the Lease,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as amended,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or a default by Tenant under this Tenant Work Letter, has occurred at any time on or before the Substantial Completion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Expansion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Premises,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	following any applicable notice and cure periods,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	then (i) in addition to all other rights and remedies granted to Landlord pursuant to the Lease,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as amended,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord shall have the right to cause Contractor to cease the construction of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Expansion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Premises (in which case, Tenant shall be responsible for any delay in the Substantial Completion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Expansion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Premises caused by such work stoppage as set forth in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section 4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of this Tenant Work Letter), and (ii) all other obligations of Landlord under the terms of this Tenant Work Letter shall be forgiven until such time as such default is cured pursuant to the terms of the Lease.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1017B925B_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_30">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	2.7&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Consulting Services.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Each Party agrees to provide the
</FONT>
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1017B925B_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_31">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Consulting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Services (as defined below) to the other Party, as reasonably requested in writing by the other Party
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	, although Tracon may, in certain instances, provide Consulting Services to satisfy regulatory and/or GMP requirements before notification of Santen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such
</FONT>
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1017B925B_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_32">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Consulting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Services may be provided through email correspondence, in-person meetings or video/audio conferences.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	In addition, Tracon may use consultants and contractors (including its contract manufacturers) to perform Consulting Services in direct support of Santen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	and shall notify
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Santen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	in advance when consultants and/or contractors are going to be used for such activities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	, including for example, batch record review,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	auditing and person in plant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	which will be coordinated by Tracon
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	rovided however, in no event shall the Consulting Service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	exceed [&#x2026;***&#x2026;]
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	hours
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	during any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	calendar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	quarter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

</FONT>
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1017B925B_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_33">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Consulting

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Services&#x201D; shall mean

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(i)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	provision of information regarding development and regulatory activities with respect to the Products and Tracon Products except for information exchanged through the JDC,
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	provision of any safety information with respect to the Products and Tracon Products at the request of a Party other than the information exchanged under a safety data exchange agreement entered into by the Parties pursuant to Section 3.2(c),
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(iii)&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

</FONT>
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1017B925B_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_34">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	and

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	provision of services related to coordination (including scheduling of activities, shipping activities and negotiation of agreements) with Tracon&#x2019;s contract manufacturer. For the purpose of provision of this
</FONT>
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1017B925B_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_36">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	clause (iv)

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	, to the extent such consultants are available
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	shall use reasonable efforts to enable Santen to have access to employees and consultants
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	of its contractors (including its contract manufacturers), as reasonably necessary to assist in connection with the shipping (including necessary support) of reagent and TRC105 sample supply for non-clinical/CMC purposes upon Santen&#x2019;s request and prior written consent

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Tracon agree
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	to use
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	best efforts
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	perform its service under the CRO MSA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	. Tracon and Santen acknowledge
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	if
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Tracon may not provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	the service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	under the CRO MSA in spite of Tracon&#x2019;s best efforts,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	such service shou
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	ld be covered by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	this amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Section 2.7 of the Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The Parties agree to adopt the following revised invoicing and payment process:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1017B925B_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_47">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	For all Consulting Services provided by Tracon to Santen and for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	reimbursement of all activities in Exhibit D-1, Tracon will invoice Santen within ten (10) days following the end of each calendar month, each invoice to contain reasonably detailed timesheets and backup documentation for all Exhibit D-1 activities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Santen agrees to pay such invoices within thirty (30) days of receipt.&nbsp;&nbsp;Santen agrees to reimburse Tracon for Consulting Services provided by Tracon employees at a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	rate of [&#x2026;***&#x2026;] per
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	hour, which rate shall be reviewed annually by the Parties.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	For Consulting Services provided by Tracon using consultants and contractors (including its contract manufacturers), Santen agrees to reimburse Tracon at the same rate that Tracon has negotiated with the consultant(s) or contractors, but if the amount is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	over [&#x2026;***&#x2026;] per
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	hour, Tracon will give advance notice to Santen.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<A NAME="TCON-20151231EX1027EADF4_HTM__GOBACK">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 16PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:16PT;">
	AMENDMENT #2
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 14PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:14PT;">
	Cooperative Research and Development Agreement #02663
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 14PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:14PT;">
	&#x201C;Clinical Development of Tracon Pharmaceuticals Inc.&#x2019;s TRC105, an anti-CD105 antibody, as an Anti-Cancer Agent&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 14PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:14PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The purpose of this amendment is to change certain terms of the above-reference Cooperative Research and Development Agreement (CRADA). These changes are reflected below, and except for these changes, all other provisions of the original CRADA remain in full force and effect. Two originals of this amendment are provided for execution; one is to remain with the National Cancer Institute (NCI) and the other with the Collaborator.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	CERTIFICATION OF PRINCIPAL
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	EXECUTIVE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	OFFICER
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	PURSUANT TO SECTION&nbsp;302 OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF 2002
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	I,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Charles P. Theuer, M.D., Ph.D.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, certify that:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1. I have reviewed this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K of TRACON Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc.;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2. Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3. Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4. The registrant&#x2019;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(e)&nbsp;and 15d-15(e)) for the registrant and have:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	a. Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	b. Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#x2019;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	c. Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#x2019;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#x2019;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	5. The registrant&#x2019;s other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#x2019;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#x2019;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	a. All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the registrant&#x2019;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial information; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	b. Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION_2"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	CERTIFICATION OF PRINCIPAL FINANCIAL OFFICER
